div.p:
This document describes the architecture
of the Endfield Industries platform in a visual way
with all the components and how they
interact with each other.

Endfield Industries focuses purely on raw
local AI inference (LLMs, TTS, STT) hosted
bare-metal on Yvonne (Mac Studio), delegating
higher-level AI Platform abstractions to
the lungmen.akn Kubernetes cluster.

g.title: Tailnet - Mesh VPN Network
Home applications cluster hosting the higher-level AI Platform
LiteLLM proxy aggregates local and remote LLM providers behind a single OpenAI-compatible API.
Extensible, feature-rich, and user-friendly self-hosted WebUI for LLMs.
Fair-code licensed workflow automation tool for connecting AI services and external APIs.
Unified gateway for routing requests to Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers.
PostgreSQL with pgvector extension for vector similarity search and storing AI embeddings.
Redis cache for messaging queues and rapid data access.
LM Studio local LLM inference server running on Apple Silicon's GPU and Neural Engine.
Kokoro FastAPI fast, local text-to-speech synthesis API.
Caddy reverse proxy exposing LM Studio and Kokoro securely on the network.
